From: Inochi Amaoto <inochiama@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 14 Nov 2025 08:38:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: Add helper for fixing RGMII PHY mode based on
 internal mac delay
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.18.2
Git-commit: 24afd7827efb7c69adfc41835390470e3eec4740

[ Upstream commit 24afd7827efb7c69adfc41835390470e3eec4740 ]

The "phy-mode" property of devicetree indicates whether the PCB has
delay now, which means the mac needs to modify the PHY mode based
on whether there is an internal delay in the mac.

This modification is similar for many ethernet drivers. To simplify
code, define the helper phy_fix_phy_mode_for_mac_delays(speed, mac_txid,
mac_rxid) to fix PHY mode based on whether mac adds internal delay.

